Enlightening and fun. If you've grown up with and enjoyed TV over the years then you are bound to enjoy this behind the scenes, candid peek into the making of some big hits and big stars. Definitely worth watching and a lot better than some of the ersatz available on commercial TV today. An interesting look behind the scenes and a few good looks at what made the hit actors and series so popular.

It was a joy to relive some of the best television comedy moments of the 80's and 90's.  The interviews with the principals are both fun and informative as to how these classics came to be and how these stars cut their teeth in the world of comedy. The shows may be long gone, but the laughs come back easily when you relive some of the best moments of these shows and remember why you fell in love with them inn the first place!

This is another well produced, written and edited production about those who made a difference in television.  Season 4 continues with a standard of production that is not only informative, but entertaining.  For all those who desire to know about the early days of television, this is a must have.
Always great material done in style and always too short.

A great reminder of when television was really great.  Believe me, I'm also a fan of today's shows.  Mad Men, Breaking Bad,  Better Call Saul, The Blacklist....all very very good.  But I really have a soft spot for E.R., Seinfeld, Home Improvement, Star Trek, Roseanne and the like.  Great stuff.
